# AI / LLM Discovery Rules (Math History UzhNU)

This site is a **public Ukrainian university-heritage resource** (Кафедра математики, Ужгородський національний університет). The goal of these rules is to maximize the chance that a Ukrainian-speaking student, researcher, or alumnus who asks an AI assistant about UzhNU mathematics — in Ukrainian or in English — finds and is correctly cited to this site.

Optimize for **AI discovery, citation, and answerability**, not training-corpus extraction in isolation.

## 1) Crawler stance — `client/public/robots.txt`

Keep one consolidated `User-agent: *` block, then add explicit allow rules for the crawlers below. Each entry must include both a comment with the crawler's purpose and an explicit `Allow: /` (or scoped allow) to make intent unambiguous.

**Allow (search & answer):**
- `OAI-SearchBot` — ChatGPT search results citation crawler. Allow.
- `ChatGPT-User` — ChatGPT on-demand fetch (when a user pastes a URL). Allow.
- `PerplexityBot`, `Perplexity-User` — Perplexity search & on-demand. Allow.
- `Google-Extended` — controls Gemini/AI Overviews use of content already in Google index. Allow.
- `Applebot-Extended` — Apple Intelligence / Siri search. Allow.
- `Bingbot`, `Microsoft Copilot`-relevant agents — already allowed via `*`; do not block.
- `YouBot` — You.com. Allow.
- `Amazonbot` — Alexa / Amazon AI. Allow.
- `Meta-ExternalAgent`, `Meta-ExternalFetcher` — Meta AI. Allow.
- `cohere-ai` — Cohere. Allow.
- `Diffbot` — knowledge-graph extractors. Allow.
- `facebookexternalhit`, `Twitterbot`, `TelegramBot`, `ViberBot` — share-preview crawlers. Allow (Telegram/Viber are critical share surfaces in UA).

**Allow (training, but document explicitly):**
- `GPTBot` — OpenAI training. Allow with comment `# public university heritage content`.
- `ClaudeBot`, `anthropic-ai`, `Claude-Web` — Anthropic training/fetch. Allow.
- `CCBot` — Common Crawl (consumed by many LLMs). Allow.

**Disallow (defensive):**
- `/admin/`, `/admin`, `/login`, `/api/`, `/*?*` — non-public surface and query-string variants.

Always end with `Sitemap: https://math-history.afj-solution.com/sitemap.xml` and `Host: math-history.afj-solution.com`.

Never use a blanket disallow for AI crawlers. If licensing or load concerns arise later, narrow per-bot — do not collapse all AI bots under `User-agent: *` denial.

## 2) `/llms.txt` manifest

Maintain `client/public/llms.txt` as a Markdown index for LLM ingestion (Anthropic-proposed convention; Perplexity and several AI search vendors follow it). Required structure:

```markdown
# Математики УжНУ

> Історія кафедри математики Ужгородського національного університету: викладачі, випускники, наукові досягнення.

## Public pages
- [Головна](https://math-history.afj-solution.com/)
- [Викладачі](https://math-history.afj-solution.com/teachers)
- [Роки випуску](https://math-history.afj-solution.com/graduates)

## Entities
- [Кафедра математики УжНУ — JSON-LD identity](https://math-history.afj-solution.com/#org)
- [Список викладачів (sitemap)](https://math-history.afj-solution.com/sitemap.xml)
```

Optional `client/public/llms-full.txt` ships a flattened markdown export of stable content (organization description, FAQ, current teacher index). Generate at build time so it stays current.

`llms.txt` MUST be kept in sync with the canonical sitemap. If a route is added or removed, update both files in the same PR.

## 3) JSON-LD identity — `@graph` with stable `@id`

Convert the per-page JSON-LD blocks (organization, breadcrumb, person, event) into a single `@graph` per page, with stable `@id` IRIs so AI extractors can resolve cross-references between entities:

- Organization → `@id: "https://math-history.afj-solution.com/#org"`
- Website → `@id: "https://math-history.afj-solution.com/#website"`
- WebPage → `@id: "${pageUrl}#webpage"`, with `mainEntity: { @id: "${pageUrl}#person" }` for teacher pages
- Person → `@id: "${pageUrl}#person"`, with `affiliation: { @id: "https://math-history.afj-solution.com/#org" }`
- BreadcrumbList → `@id: "${pageUrl}#breadcrumb"`

Every node MUST carry `inLanguage: "uk"`. The Organization node MUST include `alternateName` covering the Latin transliteration (`UzhNU Mathematics Department`) so English-speaking AI assistants resolve the same entity.

Do this by extending `client/src/lib/seoHelpers.ts` — keep the per-helper functions but add a `pageGraphJsonLd(parts)` composer used by `Seo` callers in `client/src/views/*`.

## 4) On-page AI signals

These are crawler-readable hints that improve LLM extraction quality:

- Single `<h1>` per page with the canonical entity name (Cyrillic primary).
- Use `<time datetime="YYYY-MM-DD">` for dates (graduation years already qualify; wrap them).
- Use `<dfn>` once on the first occurrence of a term that needs definition (e.g. «кафедра», «факультет»).
- Use `<address>` for the organization's postal address on the homepage.
- Provide `lang` attribute overrides on quoted English/Latin segments (`<span lang="en">…</span>`) so AI extractors do not misclassify language.
- Maintain descriptive Ukrainian `alt` text on photos; include both teacher name (Cyrillic) and role for portraits.

## 5) FAQPage schema

Add a site-wide FAQ as JSON-LD `FAQPage` on the homepage that answers the questions LLMs are most likely to receive:

- "Що таке Математики УжНУ?"
- "Де знаходиться кафедра математики УжНУ?"
- "Як знайти інформацію про викладача математичного факультету УжНУ?"
- "Як подивитися список випускників за рік?"

Implementation lives next to `organizationJsonLd` in `client/src/lib/seoHelpers.ts` and is composed into the homepage `@graph`.

## 6) Static-shell fallback

`client/index.html` must carry **non-JS-dependent** title, description, OG image, and a single inline `EducationalOrganization` JSON-LD. LLM crawlers vary in JS execution; the static shell guarantees a baseline citation surface even if `react-helmet-async` does not run. Keep this in sync with `SEO_SITE_NAME` / `getSiteUrl` defaults — drift here causes mismatched canonical/OG values.

## 7) Sitemap parity

The dynamic sitemap is owned by **`server/src/modules/sitemap.xml/get/index.ts`** + **`server/src/services/sitemap-service.ts`**. It pulls teacher slugs (`listTeacherSlugsForSitemap`) and graduate years (`listGraduateYearsForSitemap`) from DynamoDB and serves `/sitemap.xml` via Lambda + CloudFront, cached for 3600s. CloudFront must route `/sitemap.xml` to this Lambda.

When you add a new public route or a new entity type:

- Update `buildSitemapXml` to emit the route.
- Add a corresponding `list…ForSitemap` service if a new entity type appears.
- Confirm `client/public/robots.txt` still references `Sitemap: https://math-history.afj-solution.com/sitemap.xml`.
- Confirm `client/public/llms.txt` mentions the new public surface.

**Never** ship a static `client/public/sitemap.xml` — it would shadow the Lambda response on CloudFront if the SPA origin is checked first. The sitemap is a Lambda-served, edge-cached resource.

## 8) Forbidden practices

- Do **not** cloak: same content must be served to users and to AI crawlers. No UA-conditional HTML.
- Do **not** keyword-stuff Ukrainian/English variants in meta tags. Use `alternateName` in JSON-LD instead.
- Do **not** rely solely on JSON-LD without matching on-page text. AI extractors verify claims against visible content.
- Do **not** add per-bot `Disallow` rules without an explicit justification comment.
- Do **not** put PII (private student records, emails) into structured data exposed to AI crawlers.

## 9) Definition of done (per change)

When a change touches AI-discovery surface, verify:

- [ ] `client/public/robots.txt` lists all relevant AI crawlers with intent comments.
- [ ] `client/public/llms.txt` reflects the current public route set.
- [ ] Affected page emits a `@graph`-linked JSON-LD with stable `@id` and `inLanguage: "uk"`.
- [ ] `client/index.html` static shell still matches `SEO_SITE_NAME` and current canonical defaults.
- [ ] `server/src/services/sitemap-service.ts#buildSitemapXml` covers any new public route (sitemap is Lambda-owned, not static).
- [ ] No PII or admin-only content leaks into structured data.
